do this in actual fact.<br>
1. Take a 10 ft long hollow steel cylinder.It must be a at least this long to properly confine the plasma long enough,<br>
that is 1 foot in diameter <br>
for fusion to occurr , for reasons  of fusion plasma physics.<br>
2. Take a steel wire, and wind  100 large-massive steel solenoid coils around it the hollow steel cylinder.<br>
Each individual coil will be at least .34 feet ( 4 inches wide, and will be thick as well, so the steel can conduct a very large alternating electric current without melting from the<br>
electric resistance heating of the current <br>
3. Use a fuel mixture of Liquid duterium, and Tritium <br>
in it in order to create a steady state fusion<br>
rocket  engine.<br>
If you use ordinary hydrogen 1 in it or any other gas<br>
you can also operate this as a steady state magneto-hydrodynamic plasma rocket engine as well.<br>
4. Place a cooling jacket around the steel cylinder<br>
that has the soenoid coils on it. <br>
5. Place an anode at the back of the steel cylinder.<br>
6. Place a steel ring about 1 foot forward from <br>
the anode.This ring is the cathode,and  it will be laest 4 inches in diameter, and it will be also thick. <br>
So will be the steel anode.<br>
